How do I login to my member area?


Member Login 
Enter your username and password here and click the "Login" button.
                                      You now have the option to use your email address as your username as well as the 
                                      numeric id # that was assigned to you at the time of registration.
                                      Example Username's : 
youremail@domain.com OR 7152121


What if I dont remember my Information? 
If this is the case, please click on the appropriate links located here and you will be able to request your login info be sent to you via email.




Request/Reset Password
To request your Login information, please enter the email address you used at the time of registration and our system will reset your password and send you an email to that address containing your new login information.
                                      If you are unsure of which email address was used at the time of registration, please contact us and we will be happy to assist you further.







How do I search for member profiles?


We offer a few different options for you
Option #1
                                      You can use the search box located at the right side of almost every page.


Quick Search
You can enter your search terms here for quick and dirty search results.
The quick search will not give you extremely refined search results, but the more specific and clear you are with your word or term, the more refined your results will be.
note: single word searches work best


Power Search - Click here to expand
For a very refined search you can use the power search


Click here to expand and collapse
By using single words and combining the different search fields you can achieve very specific and refined search results to find exactly who you are looking for, either by Name, Location, or Occupation
note: single word searches work best, but you can use multiple combinations of these fields to achieve the most accurate results.


Browse Member Profiles
Option #2
                                      You can use the "Browse" menu.
                                      Once you hover over the browse menu click on the "Member Profiles" link




Browse Member Profiles
Once here you can browse our member profiles page by page or utilize the search bar as shown previously.







Where can I find member blogs?


You can browse through all blogs
Hover over the "Browse" menu and click on "Member Blogs" link




All Blog Posts
Once here you can browse through all our members blogs.
The Blogs are sorted by latest post made




Recent Blog Posts
Our home page will cycle through the latest blog posts our members have made.
Check back often! Our members are constantly writing up new and interest articles and opinions on various topics from business to entertainment.







How do I message a member?


Messaging a member
First you would need to find and visit a members profile page.




Member Contact Info
Once on a members profile page you may get there contact information here.
If you are not a member and have not logged into the system, you can use our internal messaging system to send this member a message.


Send them a message
You may click on the "Message this member" link to send this member a message.
Be sure to include your own contact information in your message as they will not be able to reply otherwise.







How can I become a member?


Apply for membership on our Enroll page
To become a member you must visit our Enroll page and submit an application.




Enroll Page
Please fill out the Enroll form and submit it.
Once we receive your completed application, a Stanford Who's Who representative will review your information and contact you via telephone to conduct a short interview. 
                                      Upon completion of the interview, the representative will state if your membership has been approved and then outline the details of Stanford Who's Who membership if you are selected.







